==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prehnite
<hw>Prehn"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from the
German Colonel <ets>Prehn</ets>, who first found it.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A pale green mineral occurring in crystalline
aggregates having a botryoidal or mammillary structure, and rarely in
distinct crystals. It is a hydrous silicate of alumina and
lime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prehnitic</ent>⟦br⟧
